Type of Lan: 

1) Wired LAN
2) Wireless LAN


Transmision Media:

Copper cables: uses electrical signal to send data
e.g. UTP cables: Most commonly used for connecting devices within LAN, 100m support, straight (same color) or cross cables
      same device we use cross cable
      Straight Cable:
      W/O<-------->O/W
      O<--->O
      W/G<------>W/G
      B<-------->B
      W/B<---->W/B
      G<------->G
      W/Br<------->W/Br
      Br<--------->Br
      
      for cross cable:
      replace orange with green and vice versa
      
Fiber optic cables: uses light signal
    Mostly for long distance connections
    bw switch to switch for high transfer rate
